20. quod verbis Graeca Latinis] This is a new fault in Lucilins’ style not before mentioned. See the note on S. 4. 6. Cicero's advice in respect to the consist- ency of our lives is illustrated thus: “Ut enim sermone eo debemus uti qui notus est nobis, ne ut quidam Graeca verba incul- cantes jure optimo rideamur, sic in ac- tiones omnemque vitam nullam discrepan- tiam conferre debemus '' (De Off. i. 31). ‘Seri studiorum ’ represents the Greek ὀψιμαθεῖς, to whom Theophrastus dovotes one of his least descriptive characters.
